      "side": 1,
      "message": "If this one and FetchFile are non blocking, maybe the name should be changed to something that hints this is async, e.g. EnqueueXXX, FetchAsync or something like that. In particular there\u0027s no way to know when it completed for the caller.\n\nThe more I think about it, the more I think I\u0027d prefer it to be sync (but I\u0027m not strongly for, so feel free to push back).\n\nIn the case of https://godoc.org/go.chromium.org/luci/client/archiver#Archiver.Push I decided to return a token because I needed the client to know at which stage the item is, to be able to have https://godoc.org/go.chromium.org/luci/client/archiver#Item.WaitForHashed. This is important as this permits efficient hashing (and caching of thereof) in the pipeline. This is not needed for download.",
